Privacy Policy
Last Updated: May 2026

At Maliya, we are committed to protecting your privacy and personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your data when using our application.

1. Information We Collect
a) Information You Provide Directly: • Account Information: Name, phone number, and email address when you register. • Business Data: Business name, logo, contact information, and invoice details. • Customer Data: Customer names, phone numbers (optional), and invoice details you create. • Expense and Revenue Data: Financial transactions you record in the application. • Preferences: Theme settings (dark/light), language (Arabic/English), and customized invoice details.

b) Information We Collect Automatically: • Device Information: Device type, operating system, and application version. • Usage Data: Your interactions with the application, such as features used and frequency of use. • Technical Logs: Error logs and performance data to improve the service.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the data we collect for the following purposes: • Provide Service: Create and manage your account and enable you to create invoices and track expenses. • Improve the Application: Analyze usage patterns to enhance features and fix bugs. • Communicate with You: Send important notifications, updates, and respond to your inquiries. • Security: Protect your account and data from unauthorized access and fraud. • Legal Compliance: Comply with applicable laws and regulations. • Share Invoices: Enable you to share invoices via WhatsApp (at your request only). • Personalization: Remember your preferences (theme, language, invoice settings). • Customer Support: Help you resolve technical issues and answer your questions.

3. Information Sharing
We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data to third parties. We may share your information only in the following cases: • Service Providers: With trusted service providers who help us operate the application (such as cloud hosting services), who are committed to protecting your data. • Legal Compliance: If required by law or in response to valid legal requests. • Rights Protection: To protect our rights, safety, property, or the rights of our other users. • With Your Consent: When you give us explicit permission to share your information.

4. Data Storage and Security
We take strong security measures to protect your data: • Encryption: Data is encrypted during transmission and at rest. • Secure Servers: Your data is stored on secure and protected servers. • Access Control: Access to your data is restricted to authorized personnel only. • Backup: Data is backed up regularly to prevent loss.

Note: Although we take all reasonable precautions, no system can be 100% secure. We are not responsible for security breaches resulting from circumstances beyond our control.

5. Your Rights
You have the following rights regarding your personal data: • Access: You can request a copy of the data we hold about you. • Correction: You can update or correct your personal information from within the application. • Deletion: You can request deletion of your account and all associated data. • Objection: You can object to the processing of your data for certain purposes. • Data Portability: You can request to export your data in a machine-readable format.

6. Data Retention
We retain your data as long as your account is active or as needed to provide our services. When you delete your account, we will delete all your personal data within 30 days, unless we are required to retain it for legal purposes.

7. Children's Privacy
The Maliya application is not intended for children under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we learn that we have collected data from a child without parental consent, we will take steps to delete such information.

8. Sharing Invoices via WhatsApp
When sharing an invoice via WhatsApp: • A unique web-accessible link to the invoice is generated. • The invoice is viewable by anyone with the link. • You are responsible for controlling who you share the link with.

9. Cookies and Tracking
We use tracking technologies to improve your experience: • Essential Cookies: Required for the application to function properly. • Analytical Cookies: To understand how you use the application and improve it.

Note: You can control cookies through your browser or device settings.

10. Changes to Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any material changes via the application or email. Your continued use of the application after changes means acceptance of the updated policy.

11. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about your privacy, please contact us: • WhatsApp: +9656060210 • Email: support@maliya.app

11. Your Consent
By using the Maliya application, you consent to this Privacy Policy and the terms of processing your data as described above.

